# Mobile App Performance Optimization

Improving the bundling speed and startup experience for both User and Rider mobile applications.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> - **QR Code Loading**: The slow progress bar when scanning the QR code is mostly due to missing Babel/Metro configurations and the use of `--clear` which bypasses caching.
> - **App Startup**: I will optimize the [App.tsx](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/App.tsx) logic to avoid blocking the UI while verifying tokens, making the app feel faster to open.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Phase 27: Configuration Optimization (User & Rider Apps)

#### [NEW] [babel.config.js](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/babel.config.js)
#### [NEW] [babel.config.js](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-rider-app/babel.config.js)
- Explicitly define `babel-preset-expo` to ensure stable and fast transformations.

#### [NEW] [metro.config.js](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/metro.config.js)
#### [NEW] [metro.config.js](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-rider-app/metro.config.js)
- Extend default Expo Metro config with standard optimizations.

---

### Phase 28: Initialization Optimization

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/App.tsx)
#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-rider-app/App.tsx)
- Refactor [checkToken](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-rider-app/App.tsx#52-72) to set `isLoading(false)` immediately after checking local storage.
- Perform the `authApi.getMe()` verification in the background or after the initial screen renders to reduce perceived wait time.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npx expo start` (without `--clear`) and verify bundling speed on subsequent runs.

### Manual Verification
- Scan QR code and observe the Metro progress bar speed.
- Verify that the app transitions from Splash/ActivityIndicator to the main screen faster.
